creator: WWPass
descriptionHtml:
With PassKey, you don’t need to remember usernames and passwords anymore. Just scan the authentication QR code on a website that supports WWPass and you are in. Tap the QR code in your web browser to sign in directly on your Android smartphone or tablet.

Try PassKey with PassHub – a secure and simple password manager for individuals and teams.
Join PassHub for free at http://passhub.net

– No Passwords Required
Easy-to-remember passwords get hacked all the time while strong passwords are often forgotten. The WWPass authentication technology does not rely on usernames and passwords.

– User Friendly Security
WWPass delivers state-of-the-art security that is also simple to use.
Clear and straightforward authentication experience is backed up by the robust technology resistant to hacker attacks.

– Simple Backup and Restore
You can backup you PassKey at any time using your email address. If your iPhone, iPad or iPod is lost or stolen, you can restore your PassKey on a new device. Restoring PassKey on a new device automatically blocks the previous copy of the app.

WWPass authentication can be easily integrated with any existing website or application. In fact, we already have out-of-the-box solutions for the most popular content management systems and web applications such as Wordpress, Drupal, Joomla, CAS and many others. We also have SDKs for PHP, Python, Java and .Net that simplify integration of WWPass authentication in custom projects. See http://developers.wwpass.com for more information.

Feel free to reach us at http://www.wwpass.com/contact-us if you need additional information or support.
